    "title": "Make regtest use 210000 block reward-halving schedule",
    "body": "Regtest uses 150 blocks for the reward-halving schedule. Testnet and mainnet use 210000. Why? I thought the whole point of regtest was to have a network that was essentially identical to testnet but without proof of work. If so, it does not make sense to have this parameter be different from testnet.\n\nIs there a reason that this was set to 150?\n\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/05e1c85fb687c82ae477c72d4a7e2d6b0c692167/src/chainparams.cpp#L247\n",
